  "texts": [
    "We had a third preregistered hypothesis: that the difference in reappraisal quality between GPT and humans would be significantly larger in vignettes expressing sadness, compared to anxiety or anger.",
    "This hypothesis was based on not using the most appropriate model in the analysis of Study 1, and therefore after correcting this error we no longer expected to see this difference (see SI for detailed explanation).",
    "Comparing the quality of reappraisal between humans and GPT.",
    "We explored differences in reappraisal quality between humans and GPT with a linear mixed effects model.",
    "We used the same four linear mixed effects models (for each of the quality measures) as in Study 1, which included an interaction between emotion of vignette and source of reappraisal and controlled for reappraisal length and order in which the reappraisals were displayed to the raters."
